<h2>How to Use Bitcoin at UKGC-Licensed Casinos: Step-by-Step Guide</h2>

<p>Converting Bitcoin to usable casino funds at UK-licensed operators requires a simple multi-step process. Follow this guide to safely bridge cryptocurrency and regulated gambling:</p>

<p><strong>Step 1: Choose a Crypto-Friendly E-Wallet</strong></p>

<p>Select from Revolut, Skrill, or Neteller based on your preferences. Revolut offers the most direct crypto integration with built-in exchange features. Skrill and Neteller provide established gambling payment infrastructure with lower fees for frequent transactions.</p>

<p><strong>Step 2: Set Up Your E-Wallet Account</strong></p>

<p>Register with your chosen service, providing required KYC documentation (passport or driving licence, proof of address). Verification typically completes within 24 hours. This one-time process enables unlimited future transactions.</p>

<p><strong>Step 3: Transfer Bitcoin to Your E-Wallet</strong></p>

<p>For Revolut: Use the in-app cryptocurrency feature to buy Bitcoin directly or send from external wallets to your Revolut Bitcoin address. For Skrill/Neteller: Transfer Bitcoin from your external wallet to your e-wallet's provided deposit address or use their cryptocurrency exchange partners.</p>

<p><strong>Step 4: Convert Bitcoin to GBP</strong></p>

<p>Within your e-wallet interface, convert your Bitcoin holdings to British pounds. Rates reflect current market prices plus a small conversion fee (typically 1-2%). Converted funds appear in your GBP balance instantly.</p>

<p><strong>Step 5: Deposit to Your Casino Account</strong></p>

<p>Log into your chosen UKGC-licensed casino, navigate to the cashier, and select your e-wallet as the deposit method. Enter your desired deposit amount in GBP and authenticate the transaction. Funds appear in your casino account within seconds to minutes.</p>

<p><strong>Step 6: Play and Withdraw</strong></p>

<p>Use your deposited funds for casino games or sports betting as normal. When ready to withdraw, select your e-wallet as the withdrawal method. UKGC casinos typically process e-wallet withdrawals within 24-72 hours. Once funds return to your e-wallet, you can reconvert to Bitcoin if desired.</p>

